50
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:44,000
But circumstances beyond her control led us to meeting you.

51
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:49,520
So you're not an abandoned child,

52
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:52,920
but rather a protected child."

53
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:58,120
But that person I met today, she??

54
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:02,880
She says she's sorry.

55
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:06,320
So I??

56
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,600
I feel as if I've gone back to being an abandoned child,

57
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,400
and not a protected child.

58
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,040
I'm sure

59
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:23,040
those words were there in her heart all her life.

60
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:32,160
"I'm sorry I couldn't be with you as much as I love you."

61
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:36,680
Do you really think so?

62
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,680
Try get some sleep for now.

63
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,000
I'm sure you'll feel better when you wake up.

