271
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:28,280
Do you still want to come with me?

272
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:32,000
Then play at the playground for a while.

273
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:34,880
Mommy will be right back.

274
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:38,160
Mommy, you'll be back soon, right?

275
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:39,960
Of course, I'll be back real soon.

276
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:48,000
But the thought that I'd never see you again??

277
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:50,000
genuinely??

278
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:53,160
genuinely never occurred to me.

279
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:58,800
That day, on my way back to you,

280
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:00,680
there was an accident.

281
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:04,600
Oh no??What do we do?

282
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,120
Are you alright?

283
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:08,520
It was quite a serious accident.

284
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:12,440
My Yun-je??Please??

285
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:18,280
Then because of that accident??

286
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:23,680
I lost everything because of that accident.

287
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,800
I lost you, my biggest treasure.

288
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,880
Is this true?

289
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:35,880
Then you never abandoned me??

290
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:38,000
I never abandoned you, Yun-je.

291
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,040
It may sound like an excuse to you,

292
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:44,480
but when I regained consciousness again??

293
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:49,120
Much time had passed already.

294
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:54,120
I searched for you like a crazy woman, wondering

295
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:57,920
where you were and how you were doing, but to no avail.

296
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:00,960
I didn't abandon you, Yun-je. I never??

297
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:03,160
I never abandoned you.

298
00:25:06,080 --> 00:25:07,240
I'm sorry.

299
00:25:08,120 --> 00:25:12,160
For leaving you in a foreign place,

300
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:14,120
for getting into an accident,

301
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:17,080
and for not being able to find you.

302
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:20,280
I'm sorry for everything.

303
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:31,240
After losing you, I lived a life of regret.

304
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,760
My whole life.

305
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:41,080
I know it may all sound like an excuse,

306
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:47,400
so hate me if you want and blame me if you want.

307
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,360
Still??

308
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:53,840
Won't you let me see you like this, at least?

309
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,240
Yun-je?

310
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:03,640
I??

311
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:09,960
have to get going. I'm sorry.

312
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:59,360
Why did you come back?

313
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:11,680
Can I stay here like this for a while?

314
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,280
Did you see her?

315
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:21,240
May I ask what you talked about?

316
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,880
Something I want to believe,

317
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:29,920
but I just can't.

318
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:34,160
That she hadn't abandoned me,

319
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,720
but had lost me.

320
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:43,000
Then the memories from at the orphanage??

321
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:47,080
I don't know, it's very different from what I remember.

322
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:50,480
I couldn't blame her

323
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,760
nor try understand her.

324
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:57,080
This was all when you were very young,

325
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:59,480
so your memories may have been distorted.

326
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:04,920
Let's believe in her sincerity instead of your memories.

327
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,960
I really hope I can.

328
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:31,600
My lifetime friend Nam Eun-ki,

329
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,800
it was nice seeing you tonight.

330
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:57,480
Paintings don't lie??

331
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:02,720
(Eun-ki Bastard)

332
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,080
Hey.

333
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:18,600
Hey, Sung Duk-mi. Come out for a second.

334
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:19,960
What?

335
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,920
Come out front.

336
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,280
I only need a few minutes.

337
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:25,160
What does he want?

338
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:32,640
Hey, if you collapse after running around like that at night,

339
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:34,280
that's immdiate death by freezing!

340
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,160
There's something that I just had to tell you now.

341
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,320
What is it?

342
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:41,160
Happy birthday. It's your birthday soon.

343
00:29:42,120 --> 00:29:44,040
But you came empty-handed.

344
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:45,720
I did bring you a birthday gift.

345
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:49,600
Myself.

346
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:50,880
What the??

347
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:56,680
Your best friend of 33 years who's just returned.

348
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:58,120
Nam Eun-ki.

349
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:03,120
Man, I really didn't want to bring this up

350
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:04,480
because it's embarrassing, but??

351
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:10,040
I ran away in middle school because I didn't want to do judo.

352
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:13,680
Do you remember how you dragged me home by the hair?

353
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:17,160
Gosh, what do you remember all the details for?

354
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:21,520
So I called you a total stranger,

355
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:23,120
and you almost beat me to death.

356
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:27,000
You said that's not something you say to your family.

357
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,040
Of course not.

358
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:33,440
It hurt like hell, but still, I couldn't help but smile.

359
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:39,480
Because you told me that I'm your family.

360
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:46,160
I was so, so grateful to hear that.

361
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:54,000
So I thought it'd be really nice

362
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:57,960
if things could continue to be like this, the way they are.

363
00:30:59,880 --> 00:31:01,080
But then??

364
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,520
I started liking you.

365
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,280
And I mean that.

366
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:20,920
But after spending some time apart, I came to realize this.

367
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,680
I'm just??

368
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,080
happy when you smile.

369
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:32,520
Even if it's not me who's beside you,

370
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:36,280
whether or not you're fangirling

371
00:31:36,280 --> 00:31:38,120
or whether or not someone else is beside you??

372
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:43,920
I just want you to be happy and smiling.

373
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,880
That's what I want the most.

374
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:52,240
That's enough to make us family, right?

375
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:00,440
My dear friend Sung Duk-mi,

376
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:04,400
who's brave and so beautiful when you smile??

377
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:08,080
I'm sorry I made things awkward for us.

378
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:11,400
I'm truly sorry.

379
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:20,080
You'll accept me as your friend again, right?

380
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,080
Nam Eun-ki.

381
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:28,320
Thank you for telling me this.

382
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:32,120
And thank you for coming back to me.

383
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:39,120
Still??you should give me a birthday present.

384
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:42,920
I just gave it to you. Me!

385
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,000
What would I do with you?

386
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:47,320
Tigers are stronger than lions, you know.

387
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:48,800
Are you crazy? I'm going to bring a lion here.

388
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:49,880
- Do it. - Are you sure?

389
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:50,920
I'll do a mean shoulder throw!

390
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:52,080
You must be out of your mind!

391
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:07,640
What do you think? The back of a man lost in his work??

392
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:09,240
Do I look cool?

393
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:10,920
Very cool, actually.

394
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:17,440
Si-an, I??

395
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:21,400
I've got many things to tell you.

396
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:24,440
Did Brother call you, by any chance?

397
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:32,040
How do you think he knew your number?

398
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:33,520
I know.

399
00:33:34,360 --> 00:33:37,480
I caught on a long time ago.

400
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:41,840
That you have a painful past,

401
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:44,000
and that I have a brother.

402
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:48,120
But why didn't you say anything?

403
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:54,320
Because I knew it was painful for you.

404
00:33:54,320 --> 00:33:55,440
So I waited.

405
00:33:56,720 --> 00:34:00,360
Until I grew up,

406
00:34:00,360 --> 00:34:01,560
until you could come to depend and rely on me.

407
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:06,880
And here I was, thinking you're still a baby??

408
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:11,480
Thank you, Si-an.

409
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:13,160
Did it go well with Brother?

410
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:23,800
I guess not, huh?

411
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:27,120
I did something unforgiveable, after all.

412
00:34:32,240 --> 00:34:33,240
Mom.

413
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:36,120
Yes?

414
00:34:36,120 --> 00:34:38,600
Why don't we show him all of your paintings?

415
00:34:39,720 --> 00:34:42,240
I don't think we should.

416
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:43,240
Why not?

417
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:50,080
This all happened because of those paintings.

418
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:52,040
It's too cruel.

419
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:59,520
It's Brother who should see those paintings, if not anyone else.

420
00:35:00,560 --> 00:35:01,960
He has to.

421
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:05,440
This is for him, too.

422
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:10,400
Mom.

423
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,760
Wait here.

424
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:29,440
Yes, Mr. Cha Si-an.

425
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,520
I was just about to call you, too.

426
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:34,040
We found two more of Lee Sol's works,

427
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:35,720
and expressed our interest in purchasing them.

428
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:37,440
I'll let you know once I hear back from them.

429
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:38,720
I see.

430
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,080
So that means there's just one left?

431
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,040
Yes, we're trying our best right now, so??

432
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,840
- No need for that. - Why not?

433
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:49,040
I know who has the last piece.

434
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:53,120
And I'd like Brother to see that last piece.

435
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:56,720
Could you convince him for me?

436
00:36:24,080 --> 00:36:26,560
It's this late already,

437
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:32,000
and she's walking this long a distance? My Hyo-jin is?

438
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:36,160
Secretary Kim, look up this neighborhood's safety rating.

439
00:36:38,240 --> 00:36:39,360
Mom!

440
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:44,320
Mom, you bought groceries?

441
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:47,000
Yeah, ingredients for stir-fried glass noodles and some squid.

442
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,320
Do you like squid soup?

443
00:36:48,320 --> 00:36:51,000
Yes, I like anything that you cook.

444
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,040
Let's go.

445
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:57,080
- Secretary Kim? - Yes, Director.

446
00:36:57,080 --> 00:37:00,040
Did you just hear Hyo-jin say "mom"?

447
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:01,320
Yes.

448
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:03,080
What are your thoughts?

449
00:37:03,080 --> 00:37:04,520
Why's she linking arms?

450
00:37:04,520 --> 00:37:05,680
What do you think about this?

451
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:08,080
I think??You've lost your daughter to her.

452
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:09,320
Oh my God!

453
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,000
Yes, Duk-mi.

454
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:24,920
Director, I'm sending you an address. See you there.

455
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:27,640
- What? - I just received a call.

456
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:31,000
A collector who has Lee Sol's art wants to show it to us.

457
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:32,600
It's the last piece in the series.

458
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:37,040
Hurry up, I'll be waiting.

459
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:58,080
The painting's here?

460
00:37:58,080 --> 00:38:00,960
Yes, the owner entrusted it to this cathedral.

461
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:02,960
That's why we're going to meet them here.

462
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:15,520
You're here?

463
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:20,560
Duk-mi.

464
00:38:20,560 --> 00:38:23,960
- The truth is??- She's not at fault.

465
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:26,400
I asked her to bring you here.

466
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:34,360
Mom didn't know that you were coming, either.

467
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:40,720
I'm sorry you weren't informed about this.

468
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:42,920
If this is uncomfortable,

469
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,880
you're free to go. It's alright.

470
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:45,880
Mom!

471
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,200
Director.

472
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:55,160
If it's hard to be here as Heo Yun-je,

473
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:58,080
then let's say you're here as Director Gold today.

474
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,840
We need to hold that exhibition,

475
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:02,360
and to do that we need to see the painting.

476
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:14,160
Will you show me??

477
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,800
the last piece?

478
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,160
Ms. Lee Sol.

479
00:39:57,560 --> 00:40:00,000
"Please protect this child."

480
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:04,320
It was with this prayer that I entrusted it here.

481
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,800
You don't remember, right?

482
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:09,000
This is Yun-je.

483
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:11,920
Heo Yun-je.

484
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,120
Mommy!

485
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:44,000
I'm hungry.

486
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:49,080
Mommy. Mommy.

487
00:41:15,120 --> 00:41:16,320
Mommy!

488
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:26,120
Mommy, I'm hungry.

489
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,040
Mommy.

490
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,520
Yun-je, what do you want to eat?

491
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:44,320
- Soy bean soup. - Hm?

492
00:41:44,320 --> 00:41:45,520
Soy bean soup.

493
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:51,120
Mommy, did you paint me?

494
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,320
We're smiling.

495
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:38,720
Both of us.

496
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:52,920
Very happily.

497
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:05,080
Wow!

498
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:11,800
Mommy, look at this!

499
00:43:15,640 --> 00:43:17,640
Mommy, did you see that?

500
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:23,760
Wow, so pretty!

501
00:44:37,760 --> 00:44:40,120
But... are you alright, Mr. Cha Si-an?

502
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:41,760
It must've been a big shock to you, too.

503
00:44:43,640 --> 00:44:45,440
Perhaps not as much as my mom,

504
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:47,440
but I waited for this day for a long time.

505
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:50,920
We found all of Mom's works,

506
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:53,000
and through them we found the child she'd lost.

507
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:57,120
We found my brother.

508
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:01,960
Are you an angel, by any chance?

509
00:45:01,960 --> 00:45:03,160
Please.

510
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:04,680
I do get asked that every so often.

511
00:45:06,680 --> 00:45:09,040
We owe this all to you. Thank you.

512
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:10,320
No, please.

513
00:45:11,560 --> 00:45:14,600
Ms. Lee Sol, let me introduce myself once more..

514
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:17,400
I'm Sung Duk-mi, head curator at Cheum Museum of Art.

515
00:45:17,400 --> 00:45:19,120
What brings you here at this hour?

516
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:24,440
I heard you know where the last piece is.

517
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:28,720
I'd rather not reveal??

518
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:31,120
Would you first take a look at this?

519
00:45:38,280 --> 00:45:41,600
(Cheum Museum of Art's 5th Anniversary Special Exhibition)

520
00:45:41,600 --> 00:45:43,480
Just the fragments could lead to

521
00:45:43,480 --> 00:45:46,160
different interpretations, but??

522
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:48,600
With the last piece completing the series,

523
00:45:48,600 --> 00:45:51,680
anyone who sees these paintings will know.

524
00:45:52,480 --> 00:45:54,800
The heart that's contained in these paintings.

525
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,040
The feeling of love and yearning

526
00:45:59,040 --> 00:46:01,040
for that one child.

527
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:08,800
And I really want the Director to see that.

528
00:46:09,360 --> 00:46:12,000
As a curator,

529
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:14,600
and for the happiness of a person whom I cherish a lot.

530
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:17,440
Yun-jae??

531
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:19,560
But that's not the only reason.

532
00:46:19,560 --> 00:46:22,040
I'd like it to be Cheum

533
00:46:22,040 --> 00:46:24,120
where you showcase your works

534
00:46:24,120 --> 00:46:26,520
for your debut as Lee Sol.

535
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:29,720
So please say yes.

536
00:46:38,240 --> 00:46:40,480
By any chance??

537
00:46:40,480 --> 00:46:42,840
I've been hesitating whether to ask this or not??

538
00:46:42,840 --> 00:46:44,120
What is it?

539
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:46,360
Oh, it's nothing.

540
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:48,040
What is it? Go on.

541
00:46:48,920 --> 00:46:50,920
Are you, perhaps??

542
00:46:50,920 --> 00:46:52,480
a fan of mine?

543
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:55,280
A fan?

544
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:00,120
If someone likes your music, doesn't that make them a fan?

